Screwdriver, pliers

503
00:30:54,414 --> 00:30:56,334
and a piece of wire.

504
00:30:56,413 --> 00:30:58,373
Check your watches,

505
00:30:58,453 --> 00:30:59,936
and you will see
that I will return

506
00:30:59,937 --> 00:31:01,172
with the object of my mission

507
00:31:01,252 --> 00:31:02,691
in 15 minutes or less.

508
00:31:03,132 --> 00:31:04,611
All right, let's go.

509
00:31:31,604 --> 00:31:33,124
Madam is not at home, sir.

510
00:31:33,204 --> 00:31:34,204
Thank you, Maxwell.

511
00:31:34,205 --> 00:31:36,043
I won't be needing you any more.

512
00:31:36,123 --> 00:31:37,123
Very well, sir.

513
00:32:05,476 --> 00:32:07,590
Once you learn
something when you're

514
00:32:07,591 --> 00:32:09,475
young, you just never forget it.

515
00:32:10,515 --> 00:32:12,210
Except a six-year-old kid could

516
00:32:12,211 --> 00:32:14,233
steal this one-cylinder
hair dryer.

517
00:32:28,270 --> 00:32:29,830
Quiet.

518
00:32:31,949 --> 00:32:35,309
All right, buddy, let's get this
thing outta here before I...

519
00:32:35,388 --> 00:32:39,467
Oh, hello, Mr. Hawk. What are
you doing in this little car?

520
00:32:39,547 --> 00:32:41,707
Just shut up and push.

521
00:32:42,066 --> 00:32:45,706
Certainly, Mr. Hawk. One tiny
thing, is the car out of gear?

522
00:32:46,505 --> 00:32:50,105
Of course it's out of gear,
you nitwit. Just push.

523
00:32:50,505 --> 00:32:52,184
All right, Mr. Hawk.

524
00:32:56,743 --> 00:32:58,503
Okay, push.

525
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:10,499
Hey, wait a minute. What are
you gonna do about that cab?

526
00:33:13,499 --> 00:33:16,178
Are we trying to get tough?

527
00:33:16,258 --> 00:33:18,618
Don't you dare to threaten me.

528
00:33:19,338 --> 00:33:20,977
All right, Mr. Hawk.

529
00:33:22,217 --> 00:33:23,217
Well?

530
00:33:23,256 --> 00:33:24,656
Three minutes to go.

531
00:33:26,935 --> 00:33:28,095
Oh, hello, Commissioner.

532
00:33:31,014 --> 00:33:32,974
Got a little problem.

533
00:33:33,294 --> 00:33:34,974
We gotta tow him outta here.

534
00:33:37,293 --> 00:33:39,692
Mr. Hawk, just sit
quietly this time.

535
00:33:39,773 --> 00:33:42,011
Don't touch the pedals or
the gears, understood?

536
00:33:42,052 --> 00:33:44,771
Don't order me around.
I will do as I please.

537
00:33:44,851 --> 00:33:47,930
The traffic commissioner
shall hear about this.

538
00:33:48,011 --> 00:33:49,650
I am the commissioner.

539
00:33:50,489 --> 00:33:52,889
Then what are you doing
in that monkey suit?

540
00:33:53,808 --> 00:33:56,448
The traffic commissioner would
dress in dignified clothes.

541
00:33:58,128 --> 00:34:00,647
This happens to be
my dress uniform.

542
00:34:00,727 --> 00:34:03,926
I was on my way to the ceremonies
for "I am a Policeman" day.

543
00:34:04,806 --> 00:34:06,805
Okay, let's go.

544
00:34:42,076 --> 00:34:43,476
Commissioner, call your office.

545
00:34:43,556 --> 00:34:44,915
There's been an accident.

546
00:34:44,996 --> 00:34:46,875
See the man. See the man.

547
00:34:47,236 --> 00:34:49,435
One minute to go.
He'll never make it.

548
00:34:49,515 --> 00:34:51,514
Oh, if Mr. Hawk says he'll
do something, he'll...

549
00:34:51,914 --> 00:34:53,034
Here he is.

550
00:34:56,873 --> 00:34:58,992
Get that car, dead or alive.

551
00:34:59,072 --> 00:35:00,712
Right away, sir.

552
00:35:01,872 --> 00:35:03,111
Mr. Hawk?

553
00:35:03,431 --> 00:35:07,070
If you'll sign a few
of these citations.

554
00:35:07,111 --> 00:35:09,510
Compliments of the commissioner.

555
00:35:11,149 --> 00:35:14,268
Well, he's got more
stuff than I thought.

556
00:35:15,268 --> 00:35:18,348
Yeah, I'm sorry he's going too.

557
00:35:18,667 --> 00:35:21,027
All right, I'll see
you later. Bye-bye.

558
00:35:21,187 --> 00:35:24,186
Flight 38 for Las Vegas...

559
00:35:24,226 --> 00:35:27,305
I tell you, Mother, you've never
seen Uncle Alonzo in such a rage.

560
00:35:27,425 --> 00:35:30,145
He's probably having this
airport watched right now.

561
00:35:30,184 --> 00:35:34,423
But he won't find me. I'm wearing
a disguise. A disguise...

562
00:35:34,623 --> 00:35:37,223
A beard and a moustache.

563
00:35:37,302 --> 00:35:40,422
Yes, I know, Mother. I promised I
wouldn't grow a beard when I left.

564
00:35:40,502 --> 00:35:42,421
Don't you understand?
It isn't real.

565
00:35:44,021 --> 00:35:47,380
No, I will not go back and
apologise to Uncle Alonzo.

566
00:35:47,420 --> 00:35:51,899
He is a greedy,
unscrupulous, no-good,

567
00:35:52,899 --> 00:35:55,418
thieving,

568
00:35:55,938 --> 00:36:00,857
coyote. Yes, thank you, miss. Oh.

569
00:36:01,696 --> 00:36:03,536
No, Mother, my asthma
is not coming back.

570
00:36:03,576 --> 00:36:07,335
No, nothing's the matter with me.
Everything is just fine now.

571
00:36:08,694 --> 00:36:11,574
This is the turning
point of my life.

572
00:36:11,614 --> 00:36:13,454
Uncle Alonzo used
to push me around

573
00:36:13,493 --> 00:36:15,254
and you were always
telling me what to do.

574
00:36:15,293 --> 00:36:19,452
Then I met this perfectly
wonderful girl.

575
00:36:19,572 --> 00:36:23,571
I was even afraid of her 'til now.

576
00:36:23,611 --> 00:36:25,371
I've just decided something.

577
00:36:25,450 --> 00:36:29,289
I am not going to be
a rabbit any more.

578
00:36:29,330 --> 00:36:31,209
Goodbye, Mother.

579
00:36:33,089 --> 00:36:35,088
- Ooh.
- Ooh.

580
00:36:39,127 --> 00:36:41,486
Come along, Herbie. Off to market.

581
00:36:43,046 --> 00:36:45,045
Thank you, Herbie.

582
00:36:50,444 --> 00:36:54,083
Let me see now. Half
a dozen tomatoes.

583
00:36:54,123 --> 00:36:57,443
The broccoli looked
very nice yesterday.

584
00:36:57,483 --> 00:36:59,562
What else was there?

585
00:37:14,038 --> 00:37:15,558
We've sighted the car, Mr. Hawk.

586
00:37:28,914 --> 00:37:30,874
We're moving in for the kill now.

587
00:37:31,074 --> 00:37:32,554
They're moving in
for the kill now.

588
00:37:34,673 --> 00:37:35,953
Ooh.

589
00:37:40,831 --> 00:37:43,551
What happened? You said you
were moving in for the kill.

590
00:37:43,871 --> 00:37:46,390
Negative. A little
premature, I'm afraid, sir.

591
00:37:46,431 --> 00:37:48,509
She's obviously a
very desperate woman.

592
00:37:48,590 --> 00:37:50,709
But don't worry. She
won't make it this time.

593
00:38:02,067 --> 00:38:03,865
Another of your shortcuts, Herbie?

594
00:38:14,143 --> 00:38:15,423
Where is she now?

595
00:38:15,863 --> 00:38:17,622
She's still going up and up.

596
00:38:17,663 --> 00:38:20,382
It's incredible. She's
driving like a madman.

597
00:38:32,499 --> 00:38:34,258
Oh, Herbie, behave yourself.

598
00:38:34,338 --> 00:38:36,738
You knocked my glasses off.

599
00:38:39,737 --> 00:38:40,817
Where on Earth is she?

600
00:38:41,936 --> 00:38:43,775
Don't answer it. It'll be Hawk.

601
00:38:48,694 --> 00:38:49,854
Look.

602
00:38:53,454 --> 00:38:55,813
No, Mr. Hawk, the phone
didn't ring before.

603
00:38:55,853 --> 00:38:57,013
Were you trying to reach us?

604
00:38:57,252 --> 00:38:58,812
Did you grab the car?

605
00:38:58,892 --> 00:39:00,012
Any moment now.

606
00:39:00,371 --> 00:39:03,131
There it goes, into the
Sheraton-Palace Hotel.

607
00:39:03,930 --> 00:39:05,610
The Sheraton-Palace Hotel?

608
00:39:05,811 --> 00:39:10,049
May I draw your attention
to the superb baby shrimp?

609
00:39:13,489 --> 00:39:14,968
All right, Herbie,

610
00:39:15,048 --> 00:39:17,967
but you'll never convince me this
is a shortcut to Vern's Market.

611
00:39:18,047 --> 00:39:20,246
Gentlemen, do you
have a reservation?

612
00:39:20,327 --> 00:39:21,486
There it is.

613
00:39:22,726 --> 00:39:23,965
After her. Somebody stop her.

614
00:39:24,006 --> 00:39:26,445
Don't let her get away.
Come on, let's go.

615
00:39:33,924 --> 00:39:35,609
There's only one
thing gives me the

616
00:39:35,610 --> 00:39:37,483
creeps, that's that
weird little car...

617
00:39:37,882 --> 00:39:39,242
What's the matter with you?

618
00:39:39,322 --> 00:39:40,441
There it is.

619
00:39:40,642 --> 00:39:43,241
Pull yourself together.
You're getting hysterical.

620
00:39:43,361 --> 00:39:45,281
Take two aspirins and lie down.

621
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:47,600
One of us has to keep our nerve.

622
00:39:57,037 --> 00:39:58,277
Come on, come on. Move it.

623
00:40:00,637 --> 00:40:02,476
Now we've got him.

624
00:40:04,115 --> 00:40:05,435
Stop wool gathering, Herbie.

625
00:40:05,475 --> 00:40:08,354
We really must get to the market.

626
00:40:10,714 --> 00:40:11,994
Oh, oh. Wait a minute.

627
00:40:12,394 --> 00:40:14,553
Look out. He's coming back.

628
00:40:15,393 --> 00:40:16,833
Ooh.

629
00:40:18,632 --> 00:40:19,992
Look out. Look out.

630
00:40:34,508 --> 00:40:37,867
Grandma, I was worried about
you. Is everything all right?

631
00:40:37,907 --> 00:40:40,986
Wonderful. Herbie took me for
a nice drive on the bridge.

632
00:40:41,066 --> 00:40:42,466
Let me help you.

633
00:40:42,546 --> 00:40:44,825
It's Mr. Whitfield. So
nice to see you again.

634
00:40:45,105 --> 00:40:47,185
This morning you were on
your way to Missouri.

635
00:40:47,225 --> 00:40:48,625
Nicole spoke to me.

636
00:40:48,664 --> 00:40:52,064
Grandma, Mr. Whitfield's agreed
to help us fight his uncle.

637
00:40:52,143 --> 00:40:55,343
Wonderful. Stay for dinner.

638
00:40:55,382 --> 00:40:56,782
I've already invited him.

639
00:40:56,982 --> 00:40:59,221
Why don't you take those
out to the kitchen?

640
00:40:59,302 --> 00:41:00,461
Yeah. Thank you.

641
00:41:03,101 --> 00:41:05,540
What a fine young man.

642
00:41:05,580 --> 00:41:07,260
You look so right together.

643
00:41:07,339 --> 00:41:08,459
Oh.

644
00:41:08,540 --> 00:41:10,539
Now, if there's
anything I can do...

645
00:41:10,979 --> 00:41:13,978
There is one thing, Grandma.

646
00:41:14,857 --> 00:41:17,178
Just let nature take its course.

647
00:41:17,257 --> 00:41:20,776
Oh, yes, dear. Oh, I
wouldn't want to interfere,

648
00:41:20,857 --> 00:41:22,056
not for anything.

649
00:41:22,096 --> 00:41:23,096
Oh.

650
00:41:23,256 --> 00:41:25,775
By the way, we're going to
want more broccoli for dinner.

651
00:41:25,855 --> 00:41:27,815
Will you and Willoughby
pick me up some, please?

652
00:41:27,894 --> 00:41:28,894
Sure.

653
00:41:28,935 --> 00:41:31,814
Incidentally, you ought to
drive down to the beach.

654
00:41:31,893 --> 00:41:32,893
Grandma.

655
00:41:32,934 --> 00:41:34,053
It's the most beautiful day.

656
00:41:34,533 --> 00:41:36,333
We'll just go get some broccoli.

657
00:41:37,333 --> 00:41:38,732
Yes, dear, of course.

658
00:41:42,451 --> 00:41:43,930
I'm not gonna say
another word, Herbie.

659
00:41:43,970 --> 00:41:46,249
There's nothing I can do.

660
00:41:48,970 --> 00:41:53,488
Of course, I can't help it if you
happen to have a mind of your own.

661
00:41:53,848 --> 00:41:55,288
Can I?

662
00:42:01,047 --> 00:42:04,285
I guess I should have told Mrs.
Steinmetz I don't like broccoli.

663
00:42:15,642 --> 00:42:17,562
Herbie, where are you going?

664
00:42:20,841 --> 00:42:24,720
The young lady and gentleman
have turned towards the north.

665
00:42:33,358 --> 00:42:34,988
It would appear that they're not

666
00:42:34,989 --> 00:42:37,077
immediately returning
to the firehouse.

667
00:42:37,397 --> 00:42:40,596
See that they don't. Do
anything you have to,

668
00:42:40,636 --> 00:42:43,875
but don't let them return to
that firehouse until after dark.

669
00:42:43,956 --> 00:42:44,956
Do you read me?

670
00:42:45,196 --> 00:42:46,475
Perfectly, sir.

671
00:42:49,834 --> 00:42:52,154
Oh, Grandma put him up to this.

672
00:42:52,233 --> 00:42:53,233
Where's he taking us?

673
00:42:53,233 --> 00:42:55,273
I don't know, but I
could make a guess.

674
00:43:07,469 --> 00:43:11,069
Pardon me, sir. Is this the
only road from the beach?

675
00:43:11,629 --> 00:43:12,948
Yep.

676
00:43:13,029 --> 00:43:15,908
Would you care, sir, to earn $50?

677
00:43:15,947 --> 00:43:17,187
Don't mind.

678
00:43:17,227 --> 00:43:20,306
We wish you to obstruct the road
from the beach for two hours.

679
00:43:20,386 --> 00:43:22,665
My employer is preparing
a surprise party...

680
00:43:22,746 --> 00:43:25,465
Don't explain. Just
give me the money.

681
00:43:27,945 --> 00:43:30,024
It's very romantic
here, don't you think?

682
00:43:31,344 --> 00:43:33,383
Do you know that's the
first time I've ever heard

683
00:43:33,423 --> 00:43:36,102
anyone use the word "romantic"
in a real conversation?

684
00:43:36,142 --> 00:43:39,941
I hope I wasn't being too
forward, but it is romantic.

685
00:43:40,421 --> 00:43:43,780
I think that's what
Grandma had in mind.

686
00:43:43,820 --> 00:43:47,219
She always thought the Pacific
Ocean was very romantic.

687
00:43:47,300 --> 00:43:48,659
Captain Steinmetz proposed to her

688
00:43:48,739 --> 00:43:51,259
on the beach near the
Cliff House 50 years ago.

689
00:43:56,017 --> 00:43:58,696
I'm sorry I punched you
the first time I met you.

690
00:43:58,777 --> 00:43:59,777
That's okay.

691
00:43:59,936 --> 00:44:02,815
It wasn't very ladylike to hit
you with a boiled lobster.

692
00:44:02,896 --> 00:44:03,896
It's okay.

693
00:44:04,095 --> 00:44:05,855
You can hit me back if you want.

694
00:44:06,934 --> 00:44:09,174
That isn't exactly
what I had in mind.

695
00:44:17,612 --> 00:44:18,731
Oh.

696
00:44:23,810 --> 00:44:26,930
Herbie. Oh.

697
00:44:27,849 --> 00:44:29,968
Oh, it's time we
were getting back.

698
00:44:32,568 --> 00:44:34,367
Herbie, come on.

699
00:44:35,248 --> 00:44:37,527
Leave that sea gull alone.

700
00:44:39,687 --> 00:44:40,926
Herbie.

701
00:44:41,606 --> 00:44:43,165
I wish that car would
learn to mind.

702
00:44:43,766 --> 00:44:45,724
Herbie, please.

703
00:44:46,564 --> 00:44:48,404
Herbie.

704
00:44:49,244 --> 00:44:51,283
Heel, Herbie.

705
00:44:53,923 --> 00:44:56,403
See? Just needs a firm hand.

706
00:44:56,482 --> 00:45:00,522
You know, Willoughby, sometimes
you really surprise me.

707
00:45:10,838 --> 00:45:12,598
Hey, what's happening?

708
00:45:21,836 --> 00:45:24,715
Sorry, sir. My rear axle's frozen.

709
00:45:24,955 --> 00:45:25,955
But, how're we...

710
00:45:25,995 --> 00:45:27,235
Sorry.

711
00:45:36,992 --> 00:45:38,111
No, Herbie.

712
00:45:38,391 --> 00:45:39,471
Ooh.

713
00:45:40,711 --> 00:45:42,110
Whoa.

714
00:45:46,629 --> 00:45:48,230
Oh.

715
00:45:53,708 --> 00:45:55,547
Oh.

716
00:46:01,626 --> 00:46:03,866
Oh, well, here we are.

717
00:46:11,223 --> 00:46:12,303
Ah.

718
00:46:12,383 --> 00:46:13,383
Nicole?

719
00:46:13,383 --> 00:46:16,102
Very quietly and quickly, pull
your hand back inside the car.

720
00:46:16,179 --> 00:46:17,179
Why?

721
00:46:17,181 --> 00:46:18,181
We've got company.

722
00:46:20,381 --> 00:46:24,380
That's ridiculous. Why would
a shark follow a Volkswagen?

723
00:46:24,460 --> 00:46:25,860
Because he thinks the
same thing I do.

724
00:46:25,979 --> 00:46:27,300
We're going to sink.

725
00:46:35,857 --> 00:46:37,017
Excuse me.

726
00:46:37,056 --> 00:46:38,896
Can you tell me the
way to San Francisco?

727
00:46:38,937 --> 00:46:43,095
Yeah, man. Straight up the beach
road, first left, second right.

728
00:46:43,896 --> 00:46:45,014
Thank you.

729
00:46:47,055 --> 00:46:48,654
Whoa...

730
00:47:04,050 --> 00:47:06,250
Old number 22, it's gone.

731
00:47:06,289 --> 00:47:07,689
What?

732
00:47:13,328 --> 00:47:15,207
They came with a big truck.

733
00:47:15,527 --> 00:47:17,366
Everything's gone.

734
00:47:19,566 --> 00:47:21,006
Who did it?

735
00:47:22,045 --> 00:47:23,565
It said on the truck,

736
00:47:23,925 --> 00:47:27,284
"Alonzo Hawk Van & Storage."

737
00:47:27,484 --> 00:47:29,004
Haven't you ever
jimmied a lock before?

738
00:47:29,043 --> 00:47:30,283
Of course not.

739
00:47:30,364 --> 00:47:31,763
It isn't a hobby of mine.

740
00:47:31,843 --> 00:47:33,562
Hurry. We can't just stand here.

741
00:47:38,081 --> 00:47:39,761
Good for Herbie.

742
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:43,480
Halt.

743
00:47:43,560 --> 00:47:46,000
You have been detected by
electronic surveillance.

744
00:47:46,079 --> 00:47:47,399
You are about to be surrounded

745
00:47:47,439 --> 00:47:49,998
by agents of the Alonzo
Hawk Security Service.

746
00:47:50,079 --> 00:47:51,639
Touch nothing in this warehouse

747
00:47:51,718 --> 00:47:54,037
or you will be prosecuted to
the full extent of the law.

748
00:47:54,117 --> 00:47:56,517
Don't you dare talk to
me like that, Mr. Hawk.

749
00:47:56,597 --> 00:47:58,597
I want my things back and
I'm going to have them.

750
00:47:58,676 --> 00:47:59,756
I think that's a recording.

751
00:47:59,836 --> 00:48:00,996
I don't care what it is.

752
00:48:01,036 --> 00:48:03,555
Halt. You have been...

753
00:48:03,635 --> 00:48:05,394
Let's find your things
before somebody gets here.

754
00:48:05,875 --> 00:48:08,434
By agents of the Alonzo
Hawk Security Service.

755
00:48:08,513 --> 00:48:10,193
Touch nothing in this warehouse

756
00:48:10,274 --> 00:48:13,393
or you will be prosecuted to
the full extent of the law.

757
00:48:31,148 --> 00:48:33,227
Your things aren't here.
Maybe we better...

758
00:48:44,265 --> 00:48:45,944
All right, hold it.

759
00:48:47,664 --> 00:48:49,783
Okay, get your hands up.

