He has been trying to help us.

1008
01:05:23,014 --> 01:05:25,653
But there's one thing
Herbie is afraid of.

1009
01:05:34,251 --> 01:05:36,730
Whoa.

1010
01:05:40,009 --> 01:05:43,649
Now stop, Herbie.
Don't make me do it.

1011
01:05:43,728 --> 01:05:44,728
Please, do it, Grandma.

1012
01:05:48,087 --> 01:05:50,607
Very well, Herbie.

1013
01:05:50,647 --> 01:05:53,646
It so happens that I know
this nice used car lot.

1014
01:05:55,446 --> 01:05:59,285
I'd certainly hate to call Mr.
Honest Al, the used car man.

1015
01:06:01,484 --> 01:06:03,443
Of course, you know I
never would do it.

1016
01:06:03,484 --> 01:06:05,091
And between you and
me, I don't think

1017
01:06:05,091 --> 01:06:06,443
Herbie believes I would either.

1018
01:06:06,483 --> 01:06:07,883
But it always works.

1019
01:06:13,201 --> 01:06:16,561
What a lovely morning.

1020
01:06:16,600 --> 01:06:19,280
I thoroughly enjoyed it.

1021
01:06:19,359 --> 01:06:20,879
Did we get the name
of the gentleman

1022
01:06:20,919 --> 01:06:23,719
who thinks he's going to
knock down my firehouse?

1023
01:06:24,359 --> 01:06:27,597
It was Loostgarten,

1024
01:06:27,678 --> 01:06:30,317
of the Loostgarten
Wrecking Company.

1025
01:06:30,397 --> 01:06:33,676
I'm going to write that down.
We're going to need it.

1026
01:06:35,395 --> 01:06:38,035
Well, thanks anyway for
trying Millie. Bye.

1027
01:06:38,115 --> 01:06:40,035
Millie's one of the stews who
works for Hawk's airline.

1028
01:06:40,074 --> 01:06:41,434
She can't find his address either.

1029
01:06:41,514 --> 01:06:42,514
May I say something?

1030
01:06:42,554 --> 01:06:44,713
No, I'm still mad at you for
not taking care of Grandma.

1031
01:06:44,793 --> 01:06:47,273
If we can't find out where he
lives, my idea won't work.

1032
01:06:47,433 --> 01:06:49,192
We'll just have to think
of something else.

1033
01:06:49,272 --> 01:06:50,471
I am going to say something.

1034
01:06:51,272 --> 01:06:54,311
I've sent Uncle Alonzo
a card every Christmas

1035
01:06:54,351 --> 01:06:57,830
since I was seven years old,
and here's his address.

1036
01:06:57,910 --> 01:07:00,829
Willoughby, oh. You're wonderful.

1037
01:07:02,989 --> 01:07:04,068
Right.

1038
01:07:04,468 --> 01:07:05,948
Loostgarten speaking.

1039
01:07:05,988 --> 01:07:08,027
This is Alonzo Hawk.

1040
01:07:08,587 --> 01:07:10,147
Right, Mr. Hawk.

1041
01:07:10,227 --> 01:07:12,306
Loostgarten, there's been
a slight change of plan.

1042
01:07:12,387 --> 01:07:14,786
I don't want you to knock
down that firehouse tonight.

1043
01:07:14,866 --> 01:07:17,865
Instead I want you to knock
down 343 Oleander Heights.

1044
01:07:18,105 --> 01:07:20,704
You got that? 343
Oleander Heights.

1045
01:07:20,784 --> 01:07:21,784
Right.

1046
01:07:21,824 --> 01:07:23,904
Write it down.

1047
01:07:24,663 --> 01:07:26,942
I don't want to see
you blackballed

1048
01:07:27,023 --> 01:07:28,742
in the wrecking ball business,

1049
01:07:28,823 --> 01:07:31,901
If you get what I mean.

1050
01:07:31,982 --> 01:07:32,982
You were wonderful.

1051
01:07:33,021 --> 01:07:34,181
Oh.

1052
01:07:38,620 --> 01:07:43,418
Yes... I know it's 3:00 in the
morning, but I can't sleep.

1053
01:07:43,459 --> 01:07:45,178
Well, you're my doctor, aren't ya?

1054
01:07:46,058 --> 01:07:48,412
Sometimes the
old-fashioned remedies

1055
01:07:48,413 --> 01:07:50,257
seem to work best, Mr. Hawk.

1056
01:07:50,297 --> 01:07:51,737
Have you ever tried
counting sheep?

1057
01:07:51,816 --> 01:07:53,616
Sheep.

1058
01:07:53,656 --> 01:07:56,376
Picture in your mind's eye

1059
01:07:56,455 --> 01:07:59,614
a grassy green meadow,

1060
01:07:59,695 --> 01:08:02,774
a whitewashed, three-rail fence,

1061
01:08:02,814 --> 01:08:05,853
a flock of sweet little sheep.

1062
01:08:05,933 --> 01:08:10,492
They begin to jump over
the fence. One sheep...

1063
01:08:10,691 --> 01:08:14,051
Six sheep, seven sheep,

1064
01:08:14,691 --> 01:08:18,050
eight sheep, nine sheep,

1065
01:08:19,250 --> 01:08:22,768
ten...

1066
01:09:51,626 --> 01:09:52,986
Yeah, what is it?

1067
01:09:53,146 --> 01:09:55,546
Sorry to disturb ya at this
time of night, Mr. Hawk.

1068
01:09:55,625 --> 01:09:58,505
But a guy in my job can't
afford to make mistakes.

1069
01:09:58,584 --> 01:10:00,384
What are you talking about?

1070
01:10:00,464 --> 01:10:02,344
That address you gave
me on the phone.

1071
01:10:02,423 --> 01:10:04,143
What about it?

1072
01:10:04,184 --> 01:10:07,023
343 Oleander Heights.

1073
01:10:07,063 --> 01:10:08,982
Are you sure that's
the right address?

1074
01:10:09,062 --> 01:10:11,022
Of course I'm sure, you idiot.

1075
01:10:11,061 --> 01:10:14,141
I know it as well as I
know my own address.

1076
01:10:16,340 --> 01:10:19,779
Wait a minute. It
is my own address.

1077
01:10:37,215 --> 01:10:41,654
Loostgarten. No. Not
this. This is my house.

1078
01:10:41,734 --> 01:10:43,134
You dumb jerk.

1079
01:10:43,254 --> 01:10:47,692
Loostgarten. This time
you're really through. Help.

1080
01:10:50,332 --> 01:10:52,811
You...

1081
01:11:04,728 --> 01:11:05,848
We beat him.

1082
01:11:06,128 --> 01:11:08,327
I knew he'd cave in. He just
couldn't stand the heat.

1083
01:11:11,367 --> 01:11:15,525
Hello? Oh, good morning, Mr. Hawk.

1084
01:11:16,485 --> 01:11:19,204
Well, now that it's all over, I
just had to phone you and tell you

1085
01:11:19,284 --> 01:11:21,298
how much I admire the
plucky fight you

1086
01:11:21,299 --> 01:11:23,363
put up for that sweet
little firehouse.

1087
01:11:23,763 --> 01:11:26,082
Oh, thank you, Mr. Hawk.

1088
01:11:26,243 --> 01:11:28,882
Well, what brought about
my change of heart

1089
01:11:28,962 --> 01:11:31,721
was an accident to
my own little house.

1090
01:11:31,802 --> 01:11:33,757
It only brought home
to me how terrible

1091
01:11:33,758 --> 01:11:35,761
it is to lose something
you really love.

1092
01:11:36,080 --> 01:11:38,200
What happened, Mr. Hawk?

1093
01:11:38,360 --> 01:11:40,799
Well, a very confused
man came along

1094
01:11:40,839 --> 01:11:42,439
and knocked down the
whole side of it,

1095
01:11:42,518 --> 01:11:44,478
smashed it to rubble.

1096
01:11:45,677 --> 01:11:48,397
Someone knocked down
Mr. Hawk's house.

1097
01:11:49,037 --> 01:11:51,356
Aw, what a rotten shame.

1098
01:11:51,397 --> 01:11:52,397
But it...

1099
01:11:52,476 --> 01:11:53,876
It did serve a purpose.

1100
01:11:53,915 --> 01:11:56,675
It made me realise I can't
knock down any more

1101
01:11:56,755 --> 01:11:59,434
of San Francisco's
beautiful old buildings.

1102
01:11:59,554 --> 01:12:01,257
So I don't want you
to worry that sweet,

1103
01:12:01,258 --> 01:12:02,794
little, grey head
of yours about it.

1104
01:12:02,873 --> 01:12:04,313
Is that clear?

1105
01:12:04,393 --> 01:12:06,952
Yes, Mr. Hawk. Thank
you, Mr. Hawk.

1106
01:12:07,352 --> 01:12:10,231
All right, Mrs. Steinmetz, and
I'll drop by one of these days

1107
01:12:10,272 --> 01:12:12,511
and have a cup of tea with you.

1108
01:12:12,591 --> 01:12:13,910
Bye.

1109
01:12:15,510 --> 01:12:18,270
I always said you'd do the
finer thing, Mr. Hawk.

1110
01:12:18,349 --> 01:12:21,149
What are you talking
about, fathead?

1111
01:12:21,229 --> 01:12:22,428
Giving up Hawk Plaza.

1112
01:12:22,708 --> 01:12:24,388
Are you fooled by
this phony story?

1113
01:12:24,788 --> 01:12:26,867
But, Mr. Hawk, you
can't go back on this.

1114
01:12:27,427 --> 01:12:30,786
Oh yes, I can. I can
say I was misquoted.

1115
01:12:30,867 --> 01:12:32,746
I can say they printed
the story purposefully

1116
01:12:32,786 --> 01:12:34,785
to discredit me in the
eyes of the public.

1117
01:12:34,866 --> 01:12:38,665
Well, it's an old gag. It's
out of my bag of tricks.

1118
01:12:39,024 --> 01:12:41,104
You mean we're still going
after the old lady?

1119
01:12:41,343 --> 01:12:44,263
Right for the jugular vein, baby,

1120
01:12:44,303 --> 01:12:46,503
right for the old jugular.

1121
01:12:47,662 --> 01:12:49,701
I wish Grandma would
hurry up and get here.

1122
01:12:49,742 --> 01:12:52,461
Can't start a celebration
party without her.

1123
01:12:52,501 --> 01:12:54,111
It gives us a chance
to have a quiet

1124
01:12:54,112 --> 01:12:55,460
talk. We never had one before.

1125
01:12:55,500 --> 01:12:58,300
Something always
happened. Oh, thank you.

1126
01:13:02,699 --> 01:13:04,898
Nicole, there's something
I've been wanting to say.

1127
01:13:05,658 --> 01:13:06,857
What's that, Willoughby?

1128
01:13:08,377 --> 01:13:11,496
Did I ever tell you that my
great-grandfather Whitfield

1129
01:13:11,536 --> 01:13:15,655
was one of the first men to go
over Niagara Falls in a barrel?

1130
01:13:19,414 --> 01:13:21,454
Oh, well, was he all
right afterwards?

1131
01:13:21,894 --> 01:13:23,333
I don't know. They
never found him.

1132
01:13:23,613 --> 01:13:25,253
I think I'll call Grandma.

1133
01:13:27,972 --> 01:13:30,411
The giant lobster is
very good tonight, sir.

1134
01:13:30,491 --> 01:13:32,131
Of course, no lobster.

1135
01:13:34,051 --> 01:13:35,629
I did mean to call,
dear. But I was

1136
01:13:35,630 --> 01:13:37,250
just sitting here
thinking to myself

1137
01:13:37,289 --> 01:13:39,361
what a fine time those
two young people

1138
01:13:39,362 --> 01:13:41,329
must be having without
me in the way.

1139
01:13:41,729 --> 01:13:44,448
Now listen, Grandma, I
love you very much,

1140
01:13:44,528 --> 01:13:46,487
but I've had enough
of your matchmaking.

1141
01:13:46,527 --> 01:13:48,487
Now you get over here
like you promised.

1142
01:13:48,567 --> 01:13:50,771
If I do marry Willoughby,
I'd like the

1143
01:13:50,772 --> 01:13:52,806
satisfaction of
nailing him myself.

1144
01:13:53,166 --> 01:13:55,328
Do go ahead without
me, dear. I think

1145
01:13:55,329 --> 01:13:57,604
I'll just have a quiet
evening at home.

1146
01:13:57,685 --> 01:14:00,284
Goodbye, dear.

1147
01:14:01,563 --> 01:14:06,122
Now, do go on with your wonderful
story about the cows, Mr. Judson.

1148
01:14:06,682 --> 01:14:10,041
I swear I never seen a
handsome woman like yourself

1149
01:14:10,081 --> 01:14:11,921
who had so much an
interest in cows.

1150
01:14:14,640 --> 01:14:16,800
That's quite natural, Mr. Judson.

1151
01:14:16,880 --> 01:14:19,639
After all, a cow is
not only useful,

1152
01:14:19,719 --> 01:14:22,318
but an extremely
decorative animal.

1153
01:14:22,359 --> 01:14:23,718
Ain't it just.

1154
01:14:25,997 --> 01:14:29,317
As I was saying, I got this

1155
01:14:29,396 --> 01:14:31,916
nice little 200-acre
spread up in Oregon.

1156
01:14:38,314 --> 01:14:40,633
What in tarnation
you doing that for?

1157
01:14:40,714 --> 01:14:43,913
I'm not quite sure. I think
I saw this once in a movie.

1158
01:15:22,343 --> 01:15:24,023
Oh, no.

1159
01:15:31,861 --> 01:15:35,460
Just let me get my hands on the
brute responsible for this.

1160
01:15:35,540 --> 01:15:38,020
Now. Horse whipping's
too good for him.

1161
01:15:46,057 --> 01:15:47,577
What on Earth?

1162
01:15:58,014 --> 01:15:59,214
It's Mr. Hawk.

1163
01:16:00,334 --> 01:16:01,533
Herbie. Don't you dare.

1164
01:16:05,972 --> 01:16:09,452
Oh. Every man for himself.

1165
01:16:14,970 --> 01:16:16,690
Herbie must have gone for help.

1166
01:16:16,729 --> 01:16:19,608
Hope he makes it through to
the fort. We must be cut off.

1167
01:16:19,809 --> 01:16:23,808
Okay, Steinmetz. We
know you're in there.

1168
01:16:23,888 --> 01:16:25,687
We've got you surrounded.

1169
01:16:29,966 --> 01:16:32,925
We'll give you 10 minutes to get
your stuff together and get out

1170
01:16:34,005 --> 01:16:36,525
before I grind this
dump to powder.

1171
01:16:36,884 --> 01:16:38,564
Now you hold on there, Mister.

1172
01:16:38,644 --> 01:16:40,537
This little lady's
under my personal

1173
01:16:40,538 --> 01:16:42,123
protection and she stays here.

1174
01:16:42,843 --> 01:16:44,882
Ten minutes, Steinmetz.

1175
01:16:45,203 --> 01:16:47,495
To get back to my
great-grandfather

1176
01:16:47,496 --> 01:16:48,642
at Niagara Falls,

1177
01:16:48,721 --> 01:16:52,281
I don't think I put it quite
right. What I wanted to say was,

1178
01:16:53,680 --> 01:16:57,759
though we Whitfield men
look like rabbits,

1179
01:16:57,840 --> 01:17:00,519
we have always liked challenge,

1180
01:17:00,559 --> 01:17:02,972
the scent of danger
in our nostrils,

1181
01:17:02,973 --> 01:17:04,798
the high road to adventure.

1182
01:17:04,877 --> 01:17:06,637
Yes, Willoughby?

1183
01:17:06,717 --> 01:17:09,556
That's why I want to
go on seeing you.

1184
01:17:09,637 --> 01:17:11,556
Not to deprecate your physical
attributes, certainly,

1185
01:17:11,596 --> 01:17:14,795
but because there is this
feeling of danger about you,

1186
01:17:14,835 --> 01:17:16,234
of something about to happen.

1187
01:17:19,714 --> 01:17:21,033
You're right, Willoughby.

1188
01:17:38,709 --> 01:17:40,469
Looks like we've just
picked up a friend.

1189
01:18:05,143 --> 01:18:07,422
Three minutes to go, Steinmetz.

1190
01:18:07,462 --> 01:18:09,461
This is your last chance.

1191
01:18:10,181 --> 01:18:11,541
Make your play, Hawk.

1192
01:18:12,220 --> 01:18:14,221
We're standing pat.

1193
01:18:15,260 --> 01:18:18,339
I think Captain Steinmetz would
have liked you, Mr. Judson.

1194
01:18:18,419 --> 01:18:19,819
You're his kind of man.

1195
01:18:19,899 --> 01:18:20,899
Thank you, ma'am.

1196
01:18:25,657 --> 01:18:27,536
Hey.

1197
01:19:13,166 --> 01:19:16,325
Attention. One minute to zero.

1198
01:19:17,484 --> 01:19:20,444
Gentlemen, start your engines.

1199
01:19:23,443 --> 01:19:25,643
Here come the hostiles.
We're ready for 'em.

1200
01:19:36,440 --> 01:19:39,398
I think Captain Steinmetz would
have liked you to wear this.

1201
01:19:40,678 --> 01:19:43,797
Why, I'd be proud to, little lady.

1202
01:19:45,517 --> 01:19:46,677
Mighty proud.

1203
01:19:48,957 --> 01:19:50,596
Power shovel number one, ready?

1204
01:19:50,676 --> 01:19:51,715
Ready, Mr. Hawk.

1205
01:19:52,236 --> 01:19:54,755
Full speed ahead. Go.

1206
01:20:01,833 --> 01:20:03,273
Fire.

1207
01:20:06,112 --> 01:20:07,712
Hey. Hey.

1208
01:20:09,471 --> 01:20:10,511
Stop. Help.

1209
01:20:11,111 --> 01:20:12,870
Cease fire.

1210
01:20:15,390 --> 01:20:16,989
Good shooting, Mr. Judson.

1211
01:20:17,070 --> 01:20:20,189
Thank you. That one won't
bother us for a while.

1212
01:20:20,228 --> 01:20:23,228
Hurry. Move in with the crawler.

1213
01:20:23,308 --> 01:20:24,748
All right, Mr. Hawk.

1214
01:20:26,907 --> 01:20:28,186
Fire.

1215
01:20:29,866 --> 01:20:31,665
Please, stop it. No.

1216
01:20:32,106 --> 01:20:35,184
Ceasefire.

1217
01:20:36,464 --> 01:20:38,944
There goes another one. We got
the devils on the run. Fire.

1218
01:20:41,783 --> 01:20:43,183
Oh, no.

1219
01:20:49,621 --> 01:20:51,181
Are you all right?

1220
01:20:51,461 --> 01:20:55,580
Don't worry about me, ma'am.
What we gotta worry about,

1221
01:20:55,659 --> 01:20:57,179
we're plumb outta ammunition.

1222
01:20:57,459 --> 01:20:59,939
This time we all go in together.

1223
01:21:01,098 --> 01:21:02,818
We got nothing to
regret, little lady.

1224
01:21:03,857 --> 01:21:05,417
We done our best.

1225
01:21:06,217 --> 01:21:09,216
Ready.

1226
01:21:17,254 --> 01:21:21,013
Drive. Drive. Let's get
going. Get outta here.

1227
01:22:03,843 --> 01:22:05,602
Hi, Grandma. Hi, there.

1228
01:22:08,161 --> 01:22:11,361
Why, that rascal. She's
got a man with her.

1229
01:22:11,401 --> 01:22:13,560
No wonder she wouldn't
come to our party.

1230
01:22:19,199 --> 01:22:21,678
Faster. Faster. Faster.

1231
01:22:22,758 --> 01:22:24,957
Wait a minute. Back.

1232
01:22:29,916 --> 01:22:31,355
Why don't ya look
where you're going?

1233
01:22:31,436 --> 01:22:34,354
How dare you raise your voice
to me, you myopic oaf.

1234
01:22:36,914 --> 01:22:39,074
Hey. What do you think
you're... Whoa.

1235
01:22:51,991 --> 01:22:53,630
All right, Herbie.
That's enough now.

1236
01:22:53,710 --> 01:22:57,189
You think you're gonna
make him stop? Fat chance.

1237
01:22:57,269 --> 01:22:59,868
Herbie, if you don't stop, you
won't be invited to the wedding.

1238
01:23:10,626 --> 01:23:12,585
Ah, it's you again, Mr. Hawk.

1239
01:23:13,465 --> 01:23:17,264
Save me. Save me. They're
after me. They're after me.

1240
01:23:17,824 --> 01:23:18,864
Who's after you?

1241
01:23:18,943 --> 01:23:21,103
Those little cars...
Hundreds of 'em.

1242
01:23:21,183 --> 01:23:22,742
Can't you see them, you idiot?

1243
01:23:25,022 --> 01:23:26,532
Mr. Hawk, I wonder, would you mind

1244
01:23:26,533 --> 01:23:28,221
coming down to my
place of business?

1245
01:23:28,301 --> 01:23:29,860
I would be happy to.
I would... Ooh. Ooh.

1246
01:23:30,621 --> 01:23:32,301
Ooh. Ooh.

1247
01:23:32,820 --> 01:23:34,900
And what happened then?

1248
01:23:35,020 --> 01:23:36,299
Willoughby told Herbie that

1249
01:23:36,339 --> 01:23:39,058
if he didn't stop, he wouldn't
be invited to the wedding.

1250
01:23:39,898 --> 01:23:42,818
Wait a minute. What wedding?